                        <h1>Buyer</h1>                                  
                        <IMG height=125 hspace=8 src="/print/images/photos/p13.jpg" width=165 align=left>CES is the place to take in all the products, services and technologies that drive your business, no matter if your consumer base is in-home or in-vehicle, residential or commercial. If you attend one tradeshow all year, CES has to be at the top of your list. <BR><BR>Where will you learn about this year’s hot products, trends and technologies? The answer comes in the extensive list of <A href="/print/sessions/PartnerPrograms.asp">Partner Programs</A>, <A href="/print/sessions/SuperSessions.asp">SuperSessions</A>, <A href="/print/sessions/KnowledgeTracks.asp">Knowledge Tracks</A> and <A href="/print/sessions/PartnerPrograms.asp">training and certification classes</A>. <BR><BR>
<H3>Partner Programs</H3><BR>You’ll find several partner programs with a specific interest to those directly involved in the creation, sale and installation of CE products, such as: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=CESCA_CES09">Consumer Electronics Supply Chain Academy</A> </LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=CC_CES09">Cable Conference at CES</A> with several sessions beginning Wednesday, January 7 and continuing through Thursday, January 9 </LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=CNCTS_CES09">CONNECTIONS™ Summit </A></LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=CESGP_CES09">CES Game Power Conference</A> </LI></UL><BR><BR>
<H3>CES Knowledge Tracks</H3><BR>Individual sessions are grouped together under a common theme to deliver in-depth, ground-level views of key topics uniquely relevant to buyers, specialty retailers, or professional installers such as: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=HEL_CES09">Home Entertainment and Lifestyle Technologies</A> <BR>- Alphabet Soup: Sorting out the acronyms <BR>- Wireless Home AV: Cutting all the cords<BR>- How Will We See 3D TV? <BR>- The Digital TV Transition: Are We Ready?<BR>- Accessorize Your Bottom Line: Profit Producers <BR>- Connected Digital Living: Promised Land, or Overpromised? </LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=IA_CES09">Issues and Attitudes</A><BR>- Finding Money in a Bad Economy<BR>- Home Automation for the Mass Market DTV – Bringing Down the Curtain on Analog <BR>- Design and Gender: Thinking about Sex </LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=WR_CES09">Wireless Retail </A><BR>- Now Featuring: Your Ticket To Increasing Profit Margins Through Non Traditional Accessories Sales <BR>- The Wireless Retail Landscape in 5 Years: What It Will Take To Compete <BR>- Best in Class Wireless Retailer: A Look at How to Create the Dream Wireless Retail Experience for Your Customer </LI></UL><BR><BR>
<H3>Training and Certification</H3><BR>If training and certification is your goal, CES is the only tradeshow where training and exams are available for retailers, installers and integrators in several technology disciplines such as the: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=ESPA_CES09">Electronic Systems Professional Alliance’s (ESPA) Certified-EST exam</A> </LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=DHTI_CES09">CEA-CompTIA Digital Home Technology Integrator+ (DHTI+) certification</A> </LI>
<LI class=text><A href="/print/sessions/search/trackDetail.asp?ID_track=THX_CES09">THX Certified Professional training</A> </LI></UL><BR><BR>
<H3>Exhibitors</H3><BR>While all <A href="/print/exhibitorDirectory/default.asp">2,700 exhibitors</A> will be displaying the latest products and technologies important to your bottom line, two venues of particular importance to the specialty retailer and custom installation professional are the high-performance audio and home theater exhibits in the LVCC, South Hall and The Venetian Tower Suites and Meeting Rooms.
    
